HEADWORD: Reefer
<hw>Reef"er</hw> <pr>(r⟦emac⟧f"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>One who reefs; -- a name often given to
midshipmen.</def> <rj><au>Marryat.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A close-fitting jacket or short coat of thick
cloth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A marijuana cigarette.</def>
<mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reefing</ent>⟦br⟧
